What are Linux namespaces?
Name at least 4 types and explain what each isolates.

Solution:-
Namespaces isolate system resources.

Common ones:

🔹 PID Namespace

Isolates process IDs.
Inside container:

First process = PID 1

🔹 NET Namespace

Isolates:

Network interfaces

IP addresses

Routing tables

Ports

Each container has its own network stack.

🔹 MNT Namespace

Isolates mount points.
Each container has its own root filesystem.

🔹 UTS Namespace

Isolates hostname.

🔹 IPC Namespace

Isolates shared memory and message queues.

🔹 USER Namespace

Maps container UID to different host UID.
Important for security.
